column5: Would be nice if we had more bidders up on the auction board for the Fishing for Tyler event . Plus more things to bid on . I challenge other OFC members to out do Cliff and i at this worth while cause and I say thank you to any one who does here in advance .
I would be all over that walleye guided trip if I diddnt just lake an "unseen vacation" and start my new job on the 21st.
Agreed...  The bids are still very low for what's being offered...
Times are tight for many here on OFC myself included. Id love to support but at this point its not an option..

I am unemployed and EI runs out very soon and I donated a guided day of walleye or musky...  There's gotta be some working folks that wanna guided day of fishing the st.lawrence river for musky or walleye...  And the bids on loyds spring walleye in quinte are crazy low for a 4 person trip...
Could be as simple as bidding on a package of red solo cups , if we had some ... lol
some great trips on there....im so tempted on bidding on a few....  btw when does this auction end???
No clue...  Curious about that myself...
It has'nt been decided yet ,but i am shure for most of next week yet as the event takes place next Saturday . You still have time .

One of the nicest things about this board is that we all do the best we can. Money is tight for many right now and for many putting food on the table or paying the mortgage is the necissity.  I know we've had to cut back a little this year. There are several things up for auction that I would love to bid on but just can't afford to this year and I am sure that many others are in the same boat.  Don't panic guys, there is still time and whatever we manage to raise will be appreciated as the best we could do!
